11.6.2 str_count()

Rather than a true or false, str_count() counts how many matches are in a string.

x &lt;- c("apple", "banana", "pear")
str_count(x, "p")

[1] 2 0 1

B.5 Long Lines

Keep lines under 80 characters.
Use line breaks for long function calls.


mpg |&gt;
  filter(cyl == 4, hwy &gt; 30) |&gt;
  arrange(desc(hwy))

B.6 Function Formatting

Use consistent curly brace placement.


# Good
my_function &lt;- function(x) {
  x + 1
}

# Bad
my_function &lt;- function(x){
x+1}

B.8 Piping

Each step in a pipeline goes on a new line.
Use the pipe |&gt; to connect transformations.


mpg |&gt;
  filter(cyl == 4) |&gt;
  group_by(manufacturer) |&gt;
  summarize(mean_hwy = mean(hwy))
